// Alias Generator
// Generates semantic aliases for Kodex topics by extracting and expanding keywords from titles and content.

Synonyms and abbreviations are defined externally in alias-constants. Expansion is bidirectional
and iterative until convergence. Stop words and minimum length filters apply throughout.

FUNCTION extractTitleKeywords(title, minLength) -> string[]                        EXPORT
  Lowercase and normalize the title, then split on whitespace and punctuation.
  Filter out words shorter than minLength and words in the stop-word list.
  Return the unique words as a sorted array.

---

FUNCTION extractContentKeywords(content, limit) -> string[]                        EXPORT
  Combine the conceptual and technical sections of content into one string.
  IF combined text is empty, return empty array.
  Lowercase and split on whitespace and punctuation, skip words under 3 characters and stop words.
  Count word frequency, sort by frequency descending, return the top N words up to limit.

---

FUNCTION expandWithSynonyms(keywords) -> string[]                                  EXPORT
  Starting from the keyword set, repeatedly scan the SYNONYMS table in both directions:
  if a key is in the set, add all its synonyms; if a synonym value is in the set, add its key.
  Repeat until no new keywords are added. Return the expanded set sorted.

---

FUNCTION expandWithAbbreviations(keywords) -> string[]                             EXPORT
  For each keyword, look it up in ABBREVIATIONS as a long form and add the short form.
  Also scan ABBREVIATIONS values for a match and add the corresponding long form.
  Return all keywords (original + additions) sorted.

---

FUNCTION generateAliases(name, title, content, options) -> string[]                EXPORT
  CALLS: extractTitleKeywords (alias-generator), expandWithSynonyms (alias-generator), expandWithAbbreviations (alias-generator), extractContentKeywords (alias-generator)
  Orchestrates the full alias generation pipeline with configurable options.
  1. Extract keywords from the title.
  2. IF synonyms enabled, expand the keyword set with synonym expansion.
  3. IF abbreviations enabled, expand with abbreviation expansion.
  4. IF content keywords enabled and content provided, extract and add content keywords.
  5. Remove the canonical topic name (lowercased) from the alias set.
  6. Filter aliases below minAliasLength, slice to maxAliases, and return sorted.
